`int4` and `int8` refer to OpenCL vector data types containing 4 or 8 integers respectively. In your code, the line
```c
int8 v = (int8)((int4)(vA.s0),(int4)(vA.s1));
```
(you forgot a closing bracket) contains the expression `(int4)(vA.s0)` which is equivalent to `(int4)(vA.s0, vA.s0, vA.s0, vA.s0)`, resulting in
```c
int8 v = (int8)(vA.s0, vA.s0, vA.s0, vA.s0, vA.s1, vA.s1, vA.s1, vA.s1);
```
What you want is something like this
```c
int8 v = (int8)(vA.s0, vA.s1, vA.s2, vA.s3, vA.s0, vA.s1, vA.s2, vA.s3);
```
or if you want two consecutive elements from `vecA` in `v` then use
```c
int4 vA = vecA[2*id  ];
int4 vB = vecA[2*id+1];
int8 v = (int8)(vA.s0, vA.s1, vA.s2, vA.s3, vB.s0, vB.s1, vB.s2, vB.s3);
```
Also there is no need to make `vA` `__local` since you are not sharing any data within a thread block.

