There are some steps you need to do when you want to deploy format change from jar to war.

 **1. You need to make your main method extends &quot;SpringBootServletInitializer&quot;.**

    
    @SpringBootApplication
    public class Application extends SpringBootServletInitializer {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        SpringApplication.run(Application.class, args);
        }
    }
    
    @Override 
    protected SpringApplicationBuilder configure(SpringApplicationBuilder builder) { 
        return builder.sources(SpringBootSampleApplication.class); 
    }

Please check the newly implemented **&quot;configure&quot;** method.

 **2. Change the scope of embed servlet.**

Once you start using war, **you don&#39;t need to use default tomcat in springboot**.
Open your pom.xml file and change &amp; add this content.



    &lt;dependency&gt; 
        &lt;groupId&gt;org.springframework.boot&lt;/groupId&gt; 
        &lt;artifactId&gt;spring-boot-starter-tomcat&lt;/artifactId&gt; 
        &lt;scope&gt;provided&lt;/scope&gt; 
    &lt;/dependency&gt;

You need to check **&quot;scope&quot; is set &quot;provided&quot;**.


 **3. Package in &quot;war&quot;.**

Finally, you need to package your application in war file.
Please open your pom.xml and change or add **&quot;packaging&quot;** value.


    &lt;packaging&gt;war&lt;/packaging&gt;


